1
00:00:00,334 --> 00:00:01,709
This place was a kitchen

2
00:00:02,667 --> 00:00:06,167
A small kitchen to prepare tea and other things for
the priest’s guests because this was the priest’s room

3
00:00:06,709 --> 00:00:08,959
There was also a table

4
00:00:12,209 --> 00:00:14,292
A desk table was here

5
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:18,334
He used to sit here and the others sat in front of him

6
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:20,334
This was Father’s room, here was the room

7
00:00:20,751 --> 00:00:21,959
We talked about this kitchen

8
00:00:22,334 --> 00:00:23,626
This was the guards’ room

9
00:00:24,083 --> 00:00:25,500
The guards used to sleep in it

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,292
This room, come and see

11
00:00:30,959 --> 00:00:32,250
This was the guards’ room

12
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:40,500
And this room we call in Armenian “Taganiya”

13
00:00:40,834 --> 00:00:43,584
The Taganiya room, the committee room

14
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:45,834
In Arabic they called it the committee room

15
00:00:45,876 --> 00:00:49,918
There was also a desk and chairs here, they used to sit on them

16
00:00:50,083 --> 00:00:51,542
Interviewer: Committee of what?

17
00:00:51,834 --> 00:00:53,959
Witness: Let’s say a subcommittee

18
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,042
Responsible for the church

19
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:58,959
Responsible for the Armenians in Mosul, in this room

20
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:03,751
And the other room was the accounts room

21
00:01:06,626 --> 00:01:10,500
This room, careful

22
00:01:17,751 --> 00:01:18,751
It was the same thing

23
00:01:19,792 --> 00:01:22,125
It was the same thing, there was a table here

24
00:01:22,375 --> 00:01:23,709
A desk like a table

25
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:27,584
I remember a safe here, the accounts room

26
00:01:28,042 --> 00:01:31,250
They used to pay salaries and other things, this was the accounts room

27
00:01:31,959 --> 00:01:33,500
This room was the reception room

28
00:01:34,334 --> 00:01:36,417
Our bishop’s chair was here

29
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:39,459
This whole place was full of chairs, the entire room

30
00:01:39,542 --> 00:01:41,667
Guests and others used to come

31
00:01:41,667 --> 00:01:43,292
And the reception on feast days

32
00:01:43,459 --> 00:01:45,083
After Mass we went upstairs

33
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:46,667
We drank coffee and ate chocolate

34
00:01:46,709 --> 00:01:48,959
Anyone who wanted to congratulate another did so here

35
00:01:52,209 --> 00:01:56,584
And inside was the priest’s room, Father’s room was here

36
00:01:58,375 --> 00:01:59,500
Inside, here

37
00:02:01,792 --> 00:02:03,209
This was his room

38
00:02:04,626 --> 00:02:05,626
This room

39
00:02:07,876 --> 00:02:09,042
I remember this room

40
00:02:10,125 --> 00:02:11,125
This was the priest’s room

41
00:02:12,667 --> 00:02:15,000
Interviewer: Do you remember the furniture that was inside?

42
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,209
Witness: There was a closet in this place, I still remember it now

43
00:02:20,042 --> 00:02:21,584
There was a bed here

44
00:02:21,751 --> 00:02:24,959
The cooler was here, and the TV was here, that’s what I remember

45
00:02:25,626 --> 00:02:27,459
I remember it 100%, as if it were before my eyes

46
00:02:27,626 --> 00:02:28,834
This kitchen

47
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:31,459
I have beautiful memories in this kitchen

48
00:02:33,042 --> 00:02:34,918
It was on Thursday

49
00:02:34,959 --> 00:02:36,459
We called it Good Friday

50
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:40,083
Father, may he rest in peace, every Thursday

51
00:02:40,584 --> 00:02:42,167
Karikin died in Erbil

52
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,792
And Janet’s mother used to prepare the Last Supper here

53
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,292
We deacons and the priest ate dinner here

54
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:50,876
Before we did the consecration

55
00:02:52,542 --> 00:02:54,334
These were the bathrooms, well known

56
00:02:56,459 --> 00:03:00,751
This was their daughter Janet’s room

57
00:03:01,626 --> 00:03:03,250
Of course it was a bedroom

58
00:03:05,042 --> 00:03:07,792
Interviewer: The person you mentioned, what did he do in the church?

59
00:03:07,959 --> 00:03:11,334
Witness: The priest, Father, he was the church priest

60
00:03:11,334 --> 00:03:15,709
He was the one who performed the Mass, he was the priest

61
00:03:15,918 --> 00:03:18,959
Interviewer: Did he live here?
Witness: Yes, he lived here

62
00:03:19,334 --> 00:03:20,918
This was his house and his church

63
00:03:22,375 --> 00:03:27,083
But he died before ISIS arrived

64
00:03:27,834 --> 00:03:29,667
His name was Der Karikin

65
00:03:30,125 --> 00:03:32,975
I called him Abu Janet, he was known as Abu Janet
